FBIS3-13382 "drnes049_n_94010" FBIS-NES-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 LEBANON Fadlallah: Church Blast To `Divert' Lebanese NC1103140594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1215 GMT 11 Mar 94 NC1103140594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] 'Allamah Sayyid Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah believes that the Sayyidat al-Najat explosion was meant to be a mine undercutting the Lebanese people, because what was required was to create a limited security threat that would then be turned into a political earthquake to divert the attention of the people from economic issues to concentrate on security matters. He said violating security harms both Christians and Muslims. He noted that whoever throws a bomb at a church will also do the same to a mosque. Whoever places a bomb near a cultural center somewhere will also place it in a cultural center here.
